A RESOLUTION
1 Creating the Senate Study Committee on Funding for Charter School Capital Improvements;
2 and for other purposes.
3 WHEREAS, locally approved charter schools are an integral part of Georgia's public
4 education system, providing diverse educational opportunities to students across this state;
5 and
6 WHEREAS, access to adequate facilities and capital improvements is essential to ensuring
7 that locally approved charter schools can provide high-quality learning environments; and
8 WHEREAS, traditional public schools have access to various funding sources, including
9 state and local capital outlay funds, bond financing, and the Educational Special Purpose
10 Local Option Sales Tax (E-SPLOST), while locally approved charter schools face challenges
11 in securing comparable funding for capital improvements; and
12 WHEREAS, disparities in capital funding place undue financial burdens on locally approved
13 charter schools, which often must rely on operating budgets, philanthropic contributions, or
14 private financing to secure and maintain appropriate school facilities; and
